title: China Turns to Back-Channel Diplomacy to Shore Up U.S. Ties
description: With Xi Jinping’s blessing, a Chinese delegation of policy advisers and executives met with a U.S. counterpart group ahead of the Biden-Xi summit.

title: Saudi Arabia Eyes OPEC+ Output Increase Ahead of Restrictions on Russian Oil
description: The move could help heal a rift with the Biden administration and keep energy flowing amid new attempts to blunt Russia’s oil industry over the Ukraine war.

title: Iran Soccer Players Remain Silent During Their National Anthem at World Cup
description: The team’s act appeared to be a show of solidarity with protesters at home after they received criticism from their fans.

title: Russia Steps Up Artillery Attacks in Ukraine's East
description: Moscow ramped up its efforts to capture more territory in Ukraine’s east, while Kyiv sought to win international support for its peace terms.

title: Earthquake in Indonesia Kills at Least 56
description: The 5.6-magnitude earthquake was centered in the Cianjur area in West Java. Tremors were felt in the capital city of Jakarta.

title: Heaviest Fighting in Years Breaks Out in Congo Over Control of Minerals
description: Long-simmering ethnic tensions in the eastern Democratic Republic of Congo have erupted into the most intense clashes in a decade as warring militias fight for control of the region and its mineral riches.

title: China Records First Covid-19 Deaths Since May as Cases Edge Toward Record High
description: Surging cases in Beijing and other major cities are challenging the government’s push to ease restrictions that have hit economy.

title: U.S. Presses Allies to Tighten Up Sanctions Enforcement
description: Sanctions “leakage” could undermine the pressure campaign and potentially prolong the war, officials say.

title: Iran Attacks Kurdish Groups in Iraq That It Blames for Unrest
description: The strikes come as the Islamic Republic is intensifying efforts in western Iran to suppress a two-month-old protest movement.
